      "The Creality K1 Max and Sovol SV08 occupy the same market position: large-format printers capable of printing cosplay props, big functional parts, and oversized prototypes at high speed. The K1 Max costs $599 and is designed to be accessible; the SV08 costs $479 and is built for tinkerers. Both have 300mm+ build volumes. Both run Klipper. The differences are in design philosophy, build quality consistency, and how much you want to wrangle firmware.",
